Correlation between endometriosis and pelvic pain. To evaluate the relationship between prevalence and severity of chronic pelvic pain (CPP) and stage, site, and type of endometriosis.Prospective, observational study (Canadian Task Force classification II-2).University Hospital.Of 90 consecutive women with biopsy-proved endometriosis, laparoscopy was performed in 69 for pelvic pain and in 21 for infertility or clinical and ultrasonographic suspicion of ovarian endometriosis.Preoperatively, using a 10-point visual analog scale, the severity of dysmenorrhea, CPP, and deep dyspareunia was assessed. During laparoscopy all visible endometriotic lesions were recorded and treated.Ten women (11.1%) had no pain 72 had dysmenorrhea (mild in 13, moderate in 37, severe in 22)